The Telegraph - Calcutta : Business

 Business Briefs

 Mumbai, June 14: The RBI has notified that the overseas investment limit has been raised to 300 per cent of the net worth of a company from 200 per cent. It has also raised the investment limit by listed Indian companies in the equity of foreign companies under the portfolio investment scheme to 35 per cent of the net worth from 25 per cent. 

 Mumbai, June 14: The benchmark BSE sensex today gained 201 points on aggressive purchases by institutional investors. It opened firm at 14087.91 and gradually moved up to an intra-day high of 14219.24 before ending the day at 14203.73, up by 200.69 points, or 1.43 per cent, over Wednesdays close.

